2026-04-16 12:07:11 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['switched cable indicator LED (control module)', 'series resistor for switched cable indicator LED (control module)'] hypothesis_explanation="The measured voltage indicates that the vast majority of the control module's voltage is dropping across the series resistor for the switched cable indicator LED, with only about 0.119V across the LED and 11.87V across the resistor. This suggests either the series resistor is of far too high a value or the indicator LED path is malfunctioning (open or nearly open circuit), causing a massive voltage drop at the output to the load. These components are in series with the switched output and thus directly responsible for the inability to deliver sufficient voltage to the load, matching the low output voltage symptoms despite proper relay contact continuity and input voltage. Replacing these should restore full voltage to the load output."
